<headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 27 at 4:50PM MDT  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of central Hill County
through 515 PM MDT...
At 450 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 11
miles west of Beaver Creek, or 17 miles west of Havre, moving
northeast at 35 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph, pea size hail and brief heavy
downpours.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Havre, Beaver Creek, and Kremlin.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
